----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Table [3](#Tab3){ref-type="table"} presents the mean per person under-/overcompensation under all six models for yes/no morbidity as well as separately for the seven morbidity-based risk adjusters in the risk equalization model of 2016. The mean under-/overcompensation for all groups is zero under OLS, except for the PCG group. The reason for this is that the PCG classes are not mutually exclusive, while the classes within all other risk adjusters are. For all other morbidity-based risk adjusters, the mean compensation under OLS is zero as this is a property of OLS.

